messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Listen, we're bleeding really bad.
Okay. You got attacked by people, correct?
Yes, help, help, help.
Okay, ma'am, who attacked you?
Someone came in and stabbed my mom.
Somebody came in and stabbed your mom?
Yes, they stabbed my mom and dad.
Okay, does your mom and dad need medical attention?
Yes, absolutely. We need an ambulance there now.
Do you know where the person is that attacked your parents?
No, you need to come now.
Okay, my partner is dispatching help to you now, okay?
Okay, okay.
And so you said it's both of your parents, correct?
Yes, both of my parents.
My dad has lacerations to the abdominal area.
Jeff, I'm listening to you. Just explain to me what's happening.
My mom and dad both have been stabbed.
You're in Yale, Michigan?
Yes.
Okay, hold on one second, we're getting you help.
Jeff, are both of your parents awake?
My dad is saying he can't breathe.
Is that your dad saying he can't breathe?
Yes.
And your mom, is she awake?
She's upstairs, I'm not sure.
I can hear your dad calling for help. Is your mom awake?
Yes, my mom is stabbed as well.
Okay, but is your mother awake and conscious as well?
Yes, both of them are.
Do you know where the person is that stabbed your parents?
I do not know.
Is anybody else there with you besides you and your parents?
My brother is here.
Were you in the house when this happened?
Yes, I was in the basement and my brother ran upstairs when we heard something.
Okay, and your brother's name is Jeff?
Yes.
What is your name?
Tia Skinner.
What's your callback number, Tia?
I'm not sure, I'm on my mom's phone.
Okay, just stay on the line with me.
Do you know where the weapon is that was used?
No, my brother and I were downstairs, and then I heard people yelling upstairs.
I told my brother to go upstairs because I heard screaming.
So you told your brother to go upstairs and help when you heard screaming?
Yes, and then he called you and had the phone to me.
Are you still in the basement?
Yes.
Do you know any injuries or anything that's wrong with your mother?
No, I don't know.
Just stay on the line with me. You're doing great.
Can you tell me what you heard when you were in the basement?
I heard yelling and then footsteps running down the stairs.
Then my dad came down yelling for help.
And you did not see anything that happened?
No, because we were both in the basement.
Do you know who was in the house with your parents?
No, nobody was supposed to be in the house.
What are your parents' names?
Mara and Paul Skinner.
Okay, there should be an officer on location. I want you to stay on the phone with me until you see the officer, okay?
Okay, my neighbor is here too.
Your neighbor came down to the basement?
Yes, I think he's calling someone right now.
Can you give the phone to your neighbor? Do they have any information?
No, he's on another phone.
Okay, just stay with me. We have help on the way.
Do you know where the person went who attacked your parents?
No, I just heard the yelling and then my brother ran upstairs.
Okay, we're going to stay on the line with you until help arrives.
Thank you for calling 9-1-1. We're going to stay right here with you.
